Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan has briefed SCOPA on the latest at South African Airways (SAA). Last week, Gordhan said in discussions with trade unions, they agreed to take salary cuts of up to 40% to ensure SAA’s survival. The Minister briefed the joint Portfolio Committee on Public Enterprises and the Select Committee on Public Enterprises and Communications during a virtual joint meeting on Wednesday last week. Video of Gordhan’s briefing below: 